Source: pgsqlmock
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/v-maliutin/pgSQLMock

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pgsqlmock
Architecture: all
Provides: postgresql-pgsqlmock
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, postgresql-PGVERSION-pgtap (>= 1.3.4)
Description: Mocking and faking helpers for PostgreSQL PGVERSION unit tests
 pgSQLMock extends pgTAP with helpers for mocking functions, faking tables and
 views, and restoring database objects after unit tests.
